d the GDPR, genomic \nmerit for cow conception rate (GCCR) and genomic \nmerit for milk yield (GMY) data recorded within 2 mo \nof birth to ensure that phenotypic reproductive per-\nformance did not influence ge", "relevance_score": 0.3862, "rerank_score": -7.761560440063477}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "The GDPR was enacted on May 25, 2018, not June 1, 2019.", "key_evidence": "The GDPR was enacted on May 25, 2018 according to the European Union's official website (<https://ec.europa.eu/info/law/law-topic/data-protection/general-data-protection-regulation_en>)."}, "action": "flag", "annotation": "FLAGGED \u2014 Contradicted by source (confidence 0.85): Conflicts with authoritative source"}, {"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "1761e7da", "text": "Under GDPR, data breaches must be reported to supervisory authorities within 24 hours of discovery", "normalized": "According to the GDPR, data breaches should be reported to regulatory bodies within 24 hours after detection", "claim_type": "causal", "stakes": "medium", "span_start": 50, "span_end": 136}, "status": "verified", "confidence": 0.85, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "b3ca8058d700", "source": "The-DePIN-phenomenon--Characteristics--reward-architecture--and_2026_ICT-Exp.pdf", "excerpt": "reasing the \nrisk of illicit activities such as money laundering [ 9]. Regulatory sand-\nboxes, such as those led by the UK FCA, are crucial for experimentation \nand the development of frameworks. A key legal issue involves GDPR\u2019s \nRight to be Forgotten; personal data embedded in AI model parameters ", "relevance_score": 0.4, "rerank_score": -1.6281392574310303}, {"doc_id": "d9613a65da2a", "source": "Associations-between-genomic-merit-for-daughter-pregnancy-ra_2020_Journal-of.pdf", "excerpt": "ative energy balance postpartum than \ncows that did not ovulate. Together, these data suggest \nthat selection for GDPR may hasten return to ovarian \ncycles because of less dramatic negative energy bala