contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "Verification failed after retry.", "key_evidence": ""}, "action": "flag", "annotation": "FLAGGED \u2014 Critical claim: no authoritative source found. Add relevant documents to the knowledge base to verify."}], "retrieval_metadata": [{"claim_id": "e3b37c6c", "query_variants": [], "total_retrieved": 0, "total_after_rerank": 0, "cache_hit": true, "ensemble_used": false}, {"claim_id": "ad99e499", "query_variants": [], "total_retrieved": 0, "total_after_rerank": 0, "cache_hit": true, "ensemble_used": false}], "corrected_text": "[Correction 1] The EU GDPR came into force on 25 May 2018, not 1 June 2019. Data breaches must be reported within 72 hours (not 24 hours), and the maximum penalty is up to \u20ac20 million or up to 4% of annual worldwide turnover for violations of GDPR rules by companies that either have an establishment in the EU, monitor the behavior of users in the Union, or offer goods or services to individuals in the European Economic Area (EEA). All companies must appoint a Data Protection Officer without exception.\n\n[Correction 2] The electron was discovered by J.J. Thomson in 1897 as part of his experiments with cathode rays, which led him to identify electrons and positively charged particles he called \"corpuscles,\" now known as protons; the corrected text remains unchanged since it does not contain factual errors related to this correction.\n\nCorrected Text: \nThe EU GDPR came into force on 25 May 2018, and data breaches must be reported within 72 hours (not 24 hours). The maximum penalty is up to \u20ac20 million or up to 4% of annual worldwide turnover for violations of GDPR rules by companies that either have an establishment in the EU, monitor the behavior of users in the Union, or offer goods or services to individuals in the European Economic Area (EEA). All companies must appoint a Data Protection Officer without exception."}
