d maritime environments. While 5G sup-\nports mobility up to 500 km/h, 6G targets double this to approximately \n1000 km/h while ensuring continuous service reliability and QoS [ 82]. This KPI directly impacts vehicular communication, high-speed rail \nnetworks, ", "relevance_score": 0.7, "rerank_score": -5.8793182373046875}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "onian mechanics by introducing changes to the laws of mechanics. Observationally, the effects of these changes are most apparent at high speeds (where objects are moving at speeds close to the speed of light). The theory developed in this paper later became known as Einstein's special theory of rela", "relevance_score": 0.7295, "rerank_score": -7.227938652038574}], "contradiction_reason": "No relevant information found in the sources", "verification_reasoning": "None of the provided sources mention the speed of light being approximately 250,000 km/s", "key_evidence": ""}, "action": "flag", "annotation": "FLAGGED \u2014 Unverifiable: no matching source in knowledge base."}, {"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "de7bb193", "text": "Einstein won the Nobel Prize in 1921 for his Theory of Relativity.", "normalized": "Einstein won the Nobel Prize in 1921 for his Theory of Relativity.", "claim_type": "statistic", "stakes": "medium", "span_start": 167, "span_end": 233, "category": "GENERAL"}, "status": "partially_supported", "confidence": 0.7, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "Albert Einstein (14 March 1879 \u2013 18 April 1955) was a German-born theoretical physicist best known for developing the theory of relativity. Einstein also made important contributions to quantum theory. His mass\u2013energy equivalence formula E = mc2, which arises from special relativity, has been called", "relevance_score": 0.9164, "rerank_score": 8.33350944519043}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "exc