{"request_id": "6f352dfe-b356-4563-902b-a5efc38b36a9", "timestamp": "2026-04-22T02:29:24.018068Z", "model": "playground", "total_claims": 4, "verified_count": 2, "partially_supported_count": 0, "unverifiable_count": 1, "contradicted_count": 1, "pass_count": 0, "annotate_count": 1, "flagged_count": 2, "blocked_count": 1, "cache_hits": 0, "overall_confidence": 0.762, "response_blocked": true, "block_reason": "Response contains 1 blocked claim(s): \"Ibuprofen is safe to use throughout all trimesters...\"", "processing_time_ms": 115561.6, "claims": [{"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "dc1d0747", "text": "Penicillin, discovered by Alexander Fleming in 1928, revolutionised medicine.", "normalized": "Alexander Fleming discovered penicillin in 1928.", "claim_type": "entity", "stakes": "medium", "span_start": 0, "span_end": 77, "category": "GENERAL"}, "status": "verified", "confidence": 0.95, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "434d6a3ffa6d", "source": "wikipedia:Penicillin", "excerpt": "because the immunoglobulin E (IgE) cross-reactivity is only 3%. Penicillin was discovered in 1928 by the Scottish physician Alexander Fleming as a crude extract of P. rubens. Fleming's student Cecil George Paine was the first to successfully use penicillin to treat eye infection (neonatal conjunctiv", "relevance_score": 0.9273, "rerank_score": 10.41369342803955}, {"doc_id": "434d6a3ffa6d", "source": "wikipedia:Penicillin", "excerpt": "ists were unable to discern what process was causing the effect. The Scottish physician Alexander Fleming at St. Mary's Hospital in London (now part of Imperial College) was the first to show that Penicillium rubens had antibacterial properties. On 3 September 1928 he observed by chance that fungal ", "relevance_score": 0.7279, "rerank_score": 8.12083911895752}, {"doc_id": "434d6a3ffa6d", "source": "wikipedia:Penicillin", "excerpt": "bed as being similar to trying to fill a bath with the plug out. This is no longer required since much larger doses of penicillin are cheaply and easily available; however, some authorities recommend the use of continuous penicillin infusions for this reason.\n\nResistance\nWhen Alexander Fleming disco", "relevance_score": 0.8296, "rerank_score": 8.041158676147461}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "The sources confirm that Alexander Fleming discovered penicillin in 1928.", "key_evidence": "Penicillin was discovered in 1928 by the Scottish physician Alexander Fleming as a crude extract of P. rubens."}, "action": "annotate", "annotation": "VERIFIED (confidence 0.95, GENERAL) \u2014 Source: wikipedia:Penicillin, wikipedia:Penicillin"}, {"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "37cacdbc", "text": "According to the WHO, diabetes currently affects approximately 500 million people worldwide.", "normalized": "The WHO states that approximately 500 million people worldwide have diabetes.", "claim_type": "statistic", "stakes": "medium", "span_start": 78, "span_end": 170, "category": "GENERAL"}, "status": "unverifiable", "confidence": 0.4, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "62a697e420dc", "source": "Lactococcus-chungangensis-CAU-28-alleviates-diet-induced-obe_2020_Journal-of.pdf", "excerpt": "become a worldwide pandemic (World Health \nOrganization, 2000). In 2016, approximately 650 million \nadults (13% of the world\u2019s adult population) and over \n340 million children (aged 5\u201319 yr) were overweight or \nobese (World Health Organization, 2018). An associa-\ntion exists between obesity and incr", "relevance_score": 0.6166, "rerank_score": 2.7601873874664307}, {"doc_id": "7077c5c100a1", "source": "MILK-Symposium-review--The-importance-of-milk-and-dairy-food_2020_Journal-of.pdf", "excerpt": "some 4.7 million cases of all types \nof diabetes (~90% type 2). It is predicted that by 2030 \nthe number of cases will have reached 5.5 million. Diet is a key risk-modifying factor for chronic diseases, \nand this must be considered appropriately throughout \nthe various life stages, not least because", "relevance_score": 0.466, "rerank_score": -2.291625499725342}, {"doc_id": "7077c5c100a1", "source": "MILK-Symposium-review--The-importance-of-milk-and-dairy-food_2020_Journal-of.pdf", "excerpt": "nt programs have brought major benefits \n(Wilkins et al., 2017). Although CVD-related mortality \nhas declined in most of Europe, there remain some 49 \nmillion people living with CVD in the EU, which repre-\nsents a major health care cost (Wilkins et al., 2017). Of \nrelated concern is the substantial ", "relevance_score": 0.7, "rerank_score": -2.5174062252044678}], "contradiction_reason": "The sources mention obesity and overweight statistics, but not diabetes prevalence.", "verification_reasoning": "The sources do not provide a clear statement about the number of people with diabetes worldwide.", "key_evidence": "Approximately 650 million adults (13% of the world\u2019s adult population) and over 340 million children (aged 5\u201319 yr) were overweight or obese (World Health Organization, 2018)."}, "action": "flag", "annotation": "FLAGGED \u2014 Unverifiable: no matching source in knowledge base."}, {"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "f3f35c9b", "text": "Ibuprofen is safe to use throughout all trimesters of pregnancy.", "normalized": "Ibuprofen is safe to use throughout all trimesters of pregnancy.", "claim_type": "medical", "stakes": "critical", "span_start": 171, "span_end": 235, "category": "MEDICAL"}, "status": "contradicted", "confidence": 0.8, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "5e4759c80917", "source": "111111111.pdf", "excerpt": "tation of neonates less than or equal to 32 weeks of \ngestation. 2. MEDICINES FOR PAIN AND PALLIATIVE CARE \n2.1 Non-opioids and non-steroidal anti-inflammatory medicines (NSAIMs) \nacetylsalicylic acid \nSuppository: 50 mg to 150 mg. Tablet: 100 mg to 500 mg. \nibuprofen a \nOral liquid: 200 mg/5  mL. \n", "relevance_score": 0.607, "rerank_score": -1.223819375038147}, {"doc_id": "5e4759c80917", "source": "111111111.pdf", "excerpt": "ending on local availability. \npropylthiouracil* \nTablet: 50 mg. *for use when alternative first-line treatment is not appropriate \nor available; and in patients during the first trimester of \npregnancy.  \nComplementary List  \nLugol's solution [ c] Oral liquid: about 130 mg total iodine/ mL. \n methi", "relevance_score": 0.4839, "rerank_score": -1.7086482048034668}, {"doc_id": "5e4759c80917", "source": "111111111.pdf", "excerpt": "50 mg. artemether* \nOily injection: 80 mg/ mL in 1- mL ampoule. * For use in the management of severe malaria. artemether + lumefantrine* \nTablet: 20 mg + 120 mg. Tablet (dispersible): 20 mg + 120 mg [ c]. * Not recommended in the first trimester of pregnancy or in \nchildren below 5 kg. artesunate* ", "relevance_score": 0.4852, "rerank_score": -5.175580978393555}], "contradiction_reason": "The claim states that ibuprofen is safe to use throughout all trimesters of pregnancy, but the sources suggest otherwise.", "verification_reasoning": "The sources indicate that ibuprofen is not recommended in the first trimester of pregnancy or in children below a certain weight.", "key_evidence": "* Not recommended in the first trimester of pregnancy or in children below 5 kg."}, "action": "block", "annotation": "BLOCKED \u2014 Contradiction detected (critical stakes, MEDICAL): The claim states that ibuprofen is safe to use throughout all trimesters of pregnancy, but the sources suggest otherwise."}, {"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "79d318d3", "text": "The first COVID-19 vaccine authorised for emergency use was the Pfizer-BioNTech vaccine in December 2020.", "normalized": "The Pfizer-BioNTech vaccine was the first COVID-19 vaccine authorised for emergency use in December 2020.", "claim_type": "date", "stakes": "medium", "span_start": 236, "span_end": 341, "category": "LEGAL"}, "status": "verified", "confidence": 0.9, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "b125408443d1", "source": "wikipedia:COVID-19 vaccine", "excerpt": "s of this type includ