vorstadt-Isarvorstadt, where Einstein's father and his uncle Jakob founded E", "relevance_score": 0.5682, "rerank_score": 4.768281936645508}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "secured a permanent position at the Swiss Patent Office in Bern. In 1905, he submitted a successful PhD dissertation to the University of Zurich. In 1914, he moved to Berlin to join the Prussian Academy of Sciences and the Humboldt University of Berlin, becoming director of the Kaiser Wilhelm Instit", "relevance_score": 0.7611, "rerank_score": -1.696526050567627}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "in 1987, revealed that the couple had a daughter named Lieserl. She was born in early 1902 while Mari\u0107 was visiting her parents in Novi Sad. When Mari\u0107 returned to Switzerland the child was no longer with her. What happened to Lieserl is uncertain. In a letter written in September 1903, Einstein sug", "relevance_score": 0.7284, "rerank_score": -2.1496481895446777}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "The source directly states Einstein's birthdate and location.", "key_evidence": "Albert Einstein (14 March 1879 \u2013 18 April 1955) was a German-born theoretical physicist"}, "action": "annotate", "annotation": "VERIFIED (confidence 0.92, GENERAL) \u2014 Source: wikipedia:Albert Einstein, wikipedia:Albert Einstein"}, {"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "71870d02", "text": "He won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921 for his discovery of the photoelectric effect.", "normalized": "Einstein won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921 for the photoelectric effect.", "claim_type": "statistic", "stakes": "medium", "span_start": 50, "span_end": 138, "category": "GENERAL"}, "status": "verified", "confidence": 0.88, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "ts and originality made Einstein broadly synonymous with genius. Many popular quotations are often misattributed to him.\n\nAwards and honors\nEinstein received numerous awards and honors, and in 1922, he was awarded the 1921 Nobel Prize in Physics \"for his services to Theoretical Physics, and especial", "relevance_score": 0.945, "rerank_score": 8.633898735046387}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "nces in 1920, and a Foreign Member of the Royal Society in 1921. In 1922, he was awarded the 1921 Nobel Prize in Physics \"for his services to Theoretical Physics, and especially for his discovery of the law of the photoelectric effect\".", "relevance_score": 0.8745, "rerank_score": 7.492459297180176}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "Albert Einstein (14 March 1879 \u2013 18 April 1955) was a German-born theoretical physicist best known for developing the theory of relativity. Einstein also made important contributions to quantum theory. His mass\u2013energy equivalence formula E = mc2, which arises from special relativity, has been called", "relevance_score": 0.7906, "rerank_score": 7.210531234741211}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "ially for his discovery of the law of the photoelectric effect\". At this point some physicists still regarded the general theory of relativity skeptically, and the Nobel citation displayed a degree of doubt even about the work on photoelectricity that it acknowledged: it did not assent to Einstein's", "relevance_score": 0.6187, "rerank_score": 4.947743892669678}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "ter. (Einstein was formally awarded his PhD on 15 January 1906.) Four other pieces of work that Einstein completed in 1905\u2014his famous papers on the photoelectric effect, Brownian motion, his special theory of relativity and the equivalence of mass and energy\u2014have led to the year being celebrated as ", "relevance_score": 0.5563, "rerank_score": 2.817711353302002}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "The source confirms Einstein won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921 for his services to theoretical physics, especially the photoelectric effect.", "key_evidence": "he was awarded the 1921 Nobel Prize in Physics \"for his services to Theoretical Physics, and especially for his discovery of the law of the photoelectric effect\""}, "action": "annotate", "annotation": "VERIFIED (confidence 0.88, GENERAL) \u2014 Source: wikipedia:Albert Einstein, wikipedia:Albert Einstein"}, {"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "31671627", "text": "Einstein died in Princeton, New Jersey in 1955 at the age of 76.", "normalized": "Einstein died in Princeton, New Jersey in 1955 at 76 years old.", "claim_type": "date", "stakes": "medium", "span_start": 139, "span_end": 203, "category": "GENERAL"}, "status": "verified", "confidence": 0.9, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "g at the age of 76, having continued to work until near the end. During the autopsy, the pathologist Thomas Stoltz Harvey removed Einstein's brain for preservation without the permission of his family, in the hope that the neuroscience of the future would be able to discover what made Einstein so in", "relevance_score": 0.7621, "rerank_score": 3.3822543621063232}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "ethoven and Mozart's works with members of the Zoellner Quartet. Near the end of his life, when the young Juilliard Quartet visited him in Princeton, he played his violin with them, and the quartet was \"impressed by Einstein's level of coordination and intonation\".\n\nDeath\nOn 17 April 1955, Einstein ", "relevance_score": 0.6872, "rerank_score": 3.366091728210449}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "previously been reinforced surgically by Rudolph Nissen in 1948. He took the draft of a speech he was preparing