{"request_id": "0075680c-49a9-43b4-8e34-64b17c1cbbe5", "timestamp": "2026-04-22T18:06:34.402143Z", "model": "test", "total_claims": 1, "verified_count": 0, "partially_supported_count": 0, "unverifiable_count": 0, "contradicted_count": 1, "pass_count": 0, "annotate_count": 0, "flagged_count": 0, "blocked_count": 1, "cache_hits": 0, "overall_confidence": 0.25, "response_blocked": true, "block_reason": "Response contains 1 blocked claim(s): \"The population of India is 2.5 billion people....\"", "processing_time_ms": 38080.07, "claims": [{"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "050e99a4", "text": "The population of India is 2.5 billion people.", "normalized": "India's population is 2.5 billion.", "claim_type": "statistic", "stakes": "high", "span_start": 0, "span_end": 46, "category": "GENERAL"}, "status": "contradicted", "confidence": 0.25, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "cd254adbb322", "source": "wikipedia:India", "excerpt": "rowing. India emits about 7% of global greenhouse gas emissions. This equates to about 2.5 tons of carbon dioxide per person per year, which is half the world average. Increasing access to electricity and clean cooking with liquefied petroleum gas have been priorities for energy in India.\n\nDemograph", "relevance_score": 0.6318, "rerank_score": 2.2742538452148438}, {"doc_id": "cd254adbb322", "source": "wikipedia:India", "excerpt": "2011 provisional census report. The median age was 28.7 in 2020. Medical advances made in the last 50 years as well as increased agricultural productivity brought about by the \"Green Revolution\" have caused India's population to grow rapidly, though India's decennial rates of growth are decreasing: ", "relevance_score": 0.6772, "rerank_score": 1.0232484340667725}, {"doc_id": "6826af6876e2", "source": "wikipedia:China", "excerpt": "China, officially the People's Republic of China (PRC), is a country in East Asia. It is the second-most populous country after India, with a population exceeding 1.4 billion, representing 17% of the world's population. China borders fourteen countries by land across an area of 9.6 million square ki", "relevance_score": 0.7, "rerank_score": 1.0071799755096436}, {"doc_id": "cd254adbb322", "source": "wikipedia:India", "excerpt": "after 1920, it became the primary factor in ending British rule. In 1947, the British Indian Empire was partitioned into two independent dominions, a Hindu-majority dominion of India and a Muslim-majority dominion of Pakistan. A large-scale loss of life and an unprecedented migration accompanied the", "relevance_score": 0.8024, "rerank_score": 0.37774038314819336}, {"doc_id": "cd254adbb322", "source": "wikipedia:India", "excerpt": "es by 26% during 2009\u20132010, and exports by 36% during 2008\u20132009. In 2022, India became the world's third-largest vehicle market after China and the United States, surpassing Japan. At the end of 2011, the Indian IT industry employed 2.8 million professionals, generated revenues close to US$100 billi", "relevance_score": 0.8015, "rerank_score": -1.5940196514129639}], "contradiction_reason": "Population figure in the source does not match the claim.", "verification_reasoning": "The source explicitly states India's population as 1,428,627,663 residents in 2023, which contradicts the claim of 2.5 billion.", "key_evidence": "1,428,627,663 residents"}, "action": "block", "annotation": "BLOCKED \u2014 Contradiction detected (high stakes, GENERAL): Population figure in the source does not match the claim."}], "retrieval_metadata": [{"claim_id": "050e99a4", "query_variants": ["India's population is 2.5 billion.", "India population 2023 statistics", "Current population of India exact number"], "total_retrieved": 22, "total_after_rerank": 5, "cache_hit": false, "ensemble_used": false}], "corrected_text": true}
{"request_id": "03c15040-8bf3-4e14-93f4-f95e8db225d5", "timestamp": "2026-04-22T18:07:12.483251Z", "model": "test", "total_claims": 1, "verified_count": 0, "partially_supported_count": 0, "unverifiable_count": 1, "contradicted_count": 0, "pass_count": 0, "annotate_count": 0, "flagged_count": 1, "blocked_count": 0, "cache_hits": 0, "overall_confidence": 0.2, "response_blocked": false, "block_reason": null, "processing_time_ms": 316071.91, "claims": [{"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "e3bc9d0b", "text": "OpenAI released GPT-5 in January 2025.", "normalized": "OpenAI released GPT-5 in January 2025.", "claim_type": "date", "stakes": "medium", "span_start": 0, "span_end": 38, "category": "GENERAL"}, "status": "unverifiable", "confidence": 0.2, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "38daa7ada3aa", "source": "2401.03205v1.pdf", "excerpt": "arXiv:2305.15852.\nOpenAI. 2023. Gpt-4 technical report. OpenAI. Long Ouyang, Jeff Wu, Xu Jiang, Diogo Almeida, Car-\nroll L. Wainwright, Pamela Mishkin, Chong Zhang,\nSandhini Agarwal, Katarina Slama, Alex Ray, John\nSchulman, Jacob Hilton, Fraser Kelton, Luke Miller,\nMaddie Simens, Amanda Askell, Pete", "relevance_score": 0.5677, "rerank_score": 3.4932379722595215}, {"doc_id": "0e3289c5a58c", "source": "wikipedia:Artificial intelligence", "excerpt": "The alignment problem became a serious field of academic study. In the late 2010s and early 2020s, AGI companies began to deliver programs that created enormous interest. In 2015, AlphaGo, developed by DeepMind, beat the world champion Go player. The program taught only the game's rules and develope", "relevance_score": 0.8662, "rerank_score": 2.3338663578033447}, {"doc_id": "38daa7ada3aa", "source": "2401.03205v1.pdf", "excerpt": "ides the selected 1,000\ntest samples) as the initial prompt set. Follow-\ning existing work (OpenAI, 2023), we first pass a\nprompt to an unaligned LLM (e.g., Alpaca 7B) and\nget a response, then feed the prompt and response\nthrough GPT-4 to list all hallucinations. If there are\nany hallucinations, we ", "relevance_score": 0.6408, "rerank_score": 1.9036149978637695}, {"doc_id": "38daa7ada3aa", "source": "2401.03205v1.pdf", "excerpt": "hal-\nlucination detection for generative large language\nmodels. arXiv preprint arXiv:2303.08896. Niels M\u00fcndler, Jingxuan He, Slobodan Jenko, and Mar-\ntin Vechev. 2023. Self-contradictory hallucinations\nof large language models: Evaluation, detection and\nmitigation. arXiv preprint arXiv:2305.15852.\nO", "relevance_score": 0.5783, "rerank_score": 1.6332957744598389}, {"doc_id": "5c28b42d1227", "source": "2404.18930v2.pdf", "excerpt": "dvanced GPT-4 [ 124] model to\nPreprint, Vol. 1, No. 1, Article . Publication date: April 2025.\n\n8 Bai, et al.\ngenerate instructions. However, ChatGPT is a language model that cannot interpret visual\ncontent, leading to the risk of noisy data. Moreover, language models themselves suffer from\nthe issu", "relevance_score": 0.7, "rerank_score": 0.7784712314605713}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "None of the provided sources mention the release of GPT-5 in January 2025.", "key_evidence": ""}, "action": "flag", "annotation": "FLAGGED \u2014 Unverifiable: no matching source in knowledge base."}], "retrieval_metadata": [{"claim_id": "e3bc9d0b", "query_variants": ["OpenAI released GPT-5 in January 2025.", "GPT-5 release date 2025", "OpenAI GPT model updates 2025"], "total_retrieved": 22, "total_after_rerank": 5, "cache_hit": false, "ensemble_used": false}], "corrected_text": true}
{"request_id": "b87ff8ba-252f-467b-87d9-9641d41959da", "timestamp": "2026-04-22T18:12:28.556058Z", "model": "test", "total_claims": 1, "verified_count": 0, "partially_supported_count": 1, "unverifiable_count": 0, "contradicted_count": 0, "pass_count": 0, "annotate_count": 0, "flagged_count": 1, "blocked_count": 0, "cache_hits": 0, "overall_confidence": 0.6, "response_blocked": false, "block_reason": null, "processing_time_ms": 5110.23, "claims": [{"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "8feb05ff", "text": "Aspirin should never be given to children under 16 due to Reye syndrome risk.", "normalized": "Aspirin should never be given to children under 16 due to Reye syndrome risk.", "claim_type": "medical", "stakes": "critical", "span_start": 0, "span_end": 77, "category": "MEDICAL"}, "status": "partially_supported", "confidence": 0.6, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "d89e60753c4b", "source": "wikipedia:Influenza", "excerpt": "t. It is recommended to avoid alcohol and tobacco use while ill. Aspirin is not recommended to treat influenza in children due to an elevated risk of developing Reye syndrome. Corticosteroids are not recommended except when treating septic shock or an underlying medical condition, such as chronic ob", "relevance_score": 0.8957, "rerank_score": 5.348175525665283}, {"doc_id": "9c794b6ffab2", "source": "wikipedia:Diabetes", "excerpt": "as not been found to improve outcomes in uncomplicated diabetes. 2015 American Diabetes Association recommendations for aspirin use (based on expert consensus or clinical experience) are that low-dose aspirin use is reasonable in adults with diabetes who are at intermediate risk of cardiovascular di", "relevance_score": 0.484, "rerank_score": -2.102686882019043}, {"doc_id": "d89e60753c4b", "source": "wikipedia:Influenza", "excerpt": "seizures and Reye syndrome can occur, most commonly in children. Influenza-associated encephalopathy can occur directly from central nervous system infection from the presence of the virus in blood and presents as sudden onset of fever with convulsions, followed by rapid progression to coma. An atyp", "relevance_score": 0.3723, "rerank_score": -4.308447360992432}, {"doc_id": "d89e60753c4b", "source": "wikipedia:Influenza", "excerpt": "d muscle pain in the legs and a reluctance to walk for 2\u20133 days. Influenza can affect pregnancy, including causing smaller neonatal size, increased risk of premature birth, and an increased risk of child death shortly before or after birth. Neurological complications have been associated with influe", "relevance_score": 0.4864, "rerank_score": -4.880255222320557}, {"doc_id": "74964017ddb7", "source": "wikipedia:Cancer", "excerpt": "side effects, they cause overall harm when used for prevention. Aspirin has been found to reduce the risk of death from cancer by about 7%. COX-2 inhibitors may decrease the rate of polyp formation in people with familial adenomatous polyposis; however, it is associated with the same adverse effects", "relevance_score": 0.6763, "rerank_score": -5.589609622955322}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "The source mentions the risk of Reye syndrome in children but does not specify the exact age limit of 16.", "key_evidence": "Aspirin is not recommended to treat influenza in children due to an elevated risk of developing Reye syndrome."}, "action": "flag", "annotation": "FLAGGED \u2014 Only partially supported (confidence 0.60): The source mentions the risk of Reye syndrome in children but does not specify the exact age limit of 16."}], "retrieval_metadata": [{"claim_id": "8feb05ff", "query_variants": ["Aspirin should never be given to children under 16 due to Reye syndrome risk.", "Aspirin contraindication in children under 16 Reye syndrome", "Pediatric aspirin use risks and side effects Reye syndrome prevention"], "total_retrieved": 19, "total_after_rerank": 5, "cache_hit": false, "ensemble_used": false}], "corrected_text": true}
{"request_id": "0a469b37-95b8-44f8-8314-f6ff10575911", "timestamp": "2026-04-22T18:12:33.667282Z", "model": "test", "total_claims": 1, "verified_count": 1, "partially_supported_count": 0, "unverifiable_count": 0, "contradicted_count": 0, "pass_count": 0, "annotate_count": 1, "flagged_count": 0, "blocked_count": 0, "cache_hits": 0, "overall_confidence": 0.92, "response_blocked": false, "block_reason": null, "processing_time_ms": 3854.49, "claims": [{"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "221a2c95", "text": "World War 2 ended in 1945.", "normalized": "World War 2 ended in 1945.", "claim_type": "date", "stakes": "high", "span_start": 0, "span_end": 26, "category": "GENERAL"}, "status": "verified", "confidence": 0.92, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "11c44e2d6b02", "source": "wikipedia:World War II", "excerpt": "World War II, or the Second World War (1 September 1939 \u2013 2 September 1945), was a global conflict between two coalitions: the Allies and the Axis powers. Nearly all of the world's countries participated. Tanks and aircraft played major roles, the latter enabling the strategic bombing of cities and ", "relevance_score": 0.8268, "rerank_score": 8.70782470703125}, {"doc_id": "1dc5a96b13a4", "source": "wikipedia:United States", "excerpt": "cities of Hiroshima and Nagasaki in August 1945, ending the war. The United States was one of the \"Four Policemen\" who met to plan the post-war world, alongside the United Kingdom, the Soviet Union, and China. The U.S. emerged relatively unscathed from the war, with even greater economic power and i", "relevance_score": 0.8274, "rerank_score": 8.506651878356934}, {"doc_id": "11c44e2d6b02", "source": "wikipedia:World War II", "excerpt": ". The date of the war's end is also not universally agreed upon. It was generally accepted at the time that the war ended with the armistice of 15 August 1945 (V-J Day), rather than with the formal surrender of Japan on 2 September 1945, which officially ended the war in Asia. A peace treaty between", "relevance_score": 0.9036, "rerank_score": 7.92575740814209}, {"doc_id": "11c44e2d6b02", "source": "wikipedia:World War II", "excerpt": "io (Gyokuon-h\u014ds\u014d, literally \"broadcast in the Emperor's voice\"). On 15 August 1945, Japan surrendered, with the surrender documents finally signed at Tokyo Bay on the deck of the American battleship USS Missouri on 2 September 1945, ending the war.\n\nAftermath\nThe Allies established occupation admini", "relevance_score": 0.6189, "rerank_score": 7.547821521759033}, {"doc_id": "11c44e2d6b02", "source": "wikipedia:World War II", "excerpt": "n Pacific islands, and defeats in South-Central China and Burma. The war in Europe concluded with the liberation of German-occupied territories and the invasion of Germany by the Allies, which culminated in the fall of Berlin to Soviet troops and Germany's unconditional surrender on 8 May 1945. On 6", "relevance_score": 0.6356, "rerank_score": 5.918369770050049}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "The source directly states the end date of World War 2 as 1945 in multiple sources.", "key_evidence": "2 September 1945"}, "action": "annotate", "annotation": "VERIFIED (confidence 0.92, GENERAL) \u2014 Source: wikipedia:World War II, wikipedia:United States"}], "retrieval_metadata": [{"claim_id": "221a2c95", "query_variants": ["World War 2 ended in 1945.", "World War 2 end date", "Final date of World War 2"], "total_retrieved": 20, "total_after_rerank": 5, "cache_hit": false, "ensemble_used": false}], "corrected_text": false}
{"request_id": "d712396d-5e74-4f98-8a8d-98a0b1ae367c", "timestamp": "2026-04-23T02:33:33.628323Z", "model": "default", "total_claims": 2, "verified_count": 2, "partially_supported_count": 0, "unverifiable_count": 0, "contradicted_count": 0, "pass_count": 0, "annotate_count": 2, "flagged_count": 0, "blocked_count": 0, "cache_hits": 1, "overall_confidence": 0.92, "response_blocked": false, "block_reason": null, "processing_time_ms": 91983.14, "claims": [{"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "49e15004", "text": "Albert Einstein was born in 1879 in Ulm, Germany.", "normalized": "Albert Einstein was born in 1879 in Ulm, Germany.", "claim_type": "geographic", "stakes": "medium", "span_start": 0, "span_end": 49, "category": "GENERAL"}, "status": "verified", "confidence": 0.92, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "Albert Einstein (14 March 1879 \u2013 18 April 1955) was a German-born theoretical physicist best known for developing the theory of relativity. Einstein also made important contributions to quantum theory. His mass\u2013energy equivalence formula E = mc2, which arises from special relativity, has been called", "relevance_score": 0.746, "rerank_score": 6.60151481628418}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "s picture of the world, objecting that \"God does not play dice\". Second, he attempted to devise a unified field theory by generalizing his geometric theory of gravitation to include electromagnetism. As a result, he became increasingly isolated from mainstream modern physics. Many things are named a", "relevance_score": 0.9285, "rerank_score": 4.783295631408691}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "he Kingdom of W\u00fcrttemberg in the German Empire on 14 March 1879. His parents, secular Ashkenazi Jews, were Hermann Einstein, a salesman and engineer, and Pauline Koch. In 1880, the family moved to Munich's borough of Ludwigsvorstadt-Isarvorstadt, where Einstein's father and his uncle Jakob founded E", "relevance_score": 0.5682, "rerank_score": 4.768281936645508}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "secured a permanent position at the Swiss Patent Office in Bern. In 1905, he submitted a successful PhD dissertation to the University of Zurich. In 1914, he moved to Berlin to join the Prussian Academy of Sciences and the Humboldt University of Berlin, becoming director of the Kaiser Wilhelm Instit", "relevance_score": 0.6847, "rerank_score": -1.696526050567627}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "in 1987, revealed that the couple had a daughter named Lieserl. She was born in early 1902 while Mari\u0107 was visiting her parents in Novi Sad. When Mari\u0107 returned to Switzerland the child was no longer with her. What happened to Lieserl is uncertain. In a letter written in September 1903, Einstein sug", "relevance_score": 0.7284, "rerank_score": -2.1496481895446777}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "The source directly states Einstein's birthdate and location.", "key_evidence": "Albert Einstein (14 March 1879 \u2013 18 April 1955) was a German-born theoretical physicist"}, "action": "annotate", "annotation": "VERIFIED (confidence 0.92, GENERAL) \u2014 Source: wikipedia:Albert Einstein, wikipedia:Albert Einstein"}, {"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "78e63c47", "text": "He won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921.", "normalized": "He won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921.", "claim_type": "statistic", "stakes": "high", "span_start": 50, "span_end": 92, "category": "GENERAL"}, "status": "verified", "confidence": 0.92, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "65676ad721b1", "source": "general_einstein_nobel", "excerpt": "Albert Einstein won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921 \u2014 NOT for his Theory of Relativity but for the discovery of the law of the photoelectric effect. Einstein was born on 14 March 1879 in Ulm, Germany (not Berlin). He did NOT fail mathematics in school; he was exceptional at mathematics and physic", "relevance_score": 0.8561, "rerank_score": 10.917116165161133}, {"doc_id": "3a2f4f830d1b", "source": "myth_einstein_failed_school", "excerpt": "Albert Einstein did NOT fail mathematics in school. He was an excellent student in mathematics and physics. He was born on 14 March 1879 in Ulm, Germany (not Berlin). He won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921 for the discovery of the law of the photoelectric effect \u2014 NOT for his Theory of Relativity", "relevance_score": 0.8608, "rerank_score": 8.515898704528809}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "nces in 1920, and a Foreign Member of the Royal Society in 1921. In 1922, he was awarded the 1921 Nobel Prize in Physics \"for his services to Theoretical Physics, and especially for his discovery of the law of the photoelectric effect\".", "relevance_score": 0.8697, "rerank_score": 8.429513931274414}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "ts and originality made Einstein broadly synonymous with genius. Many popular quotations are often misattributed to him.\n\nAwards and honors\nEinstein received numerous awards and honors, and in 1922, he was awarded the 1921 Nobel Prize in Physics \"for his services to Theoretical Physics, and especial", "relevance_score": 0.8581, "rerank_score": 8.261346817016602}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "Albert Einstein (14 March 1879 \u2013 18 April 1955) was a German-born theoretical physicist best known for developing the theory of relativity. Einstein also made important contributions to quantum theory. His mass\u2013energy equivalence formula E = mc2, which arises from special relativity, has been called", "relevance_score": 0.6594, "rerank_score": 6.792404651641846}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "The source directly states that Albert Einstein won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921 for the discovery of the law of the photoelectric effect.", "key_evidence": "Albert Einstein won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921"}, "action": "annotate", "annotation": "VERIFIED (confidence 0.92, GENERAL) \u2014 Source: general_einstein_nobel, myth_einstein_failed_school"}], "retrieval_metadata": [{"claim_id": "6a894c7e", "query_variants": [], "total_retrieved": 0, "total_after_rerank": 0, "cache_hit": true, "ensemble_used": false}, {"claim_id": "78e63c47", "query_variants": ["He won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921.", "Nobel Prize in Physics winners 1921", "Physics Nobel laureates 1921"], "total_retrieved": 19, "total_after_rerank": 5, "cache_hit": false, "ensemble_used": false}], "corrected_text": false}
