n on 14 March 1879 in Ulm, Germany (not Berlin). He did NOT fail mathematics in school; he was exceptional at mathematics and physic", "relevance_score": 0.8561, "rerank_score": 10.917116165161133}, {"doc_id": "3a2f4f830d1b", "source": "myth_einstein_failed_school", "excerpt": "Albert Einstein did NOT fail mathematics in school. He was an excellent student in mathematics and physics. He was born on 14 March 1879 in Ulm, Germany (not Berlin). He won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921 for the discovery of the law of the photoelectric effect \u2014 NOT for his Theory of Relativity", "relevance_score": 0.8608, "rerank_score": 8.515898704528809}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "nces in 1920, and a Foreign Member of the Royal Society in 1921. In 1922, he was awarded the 1921 Nobel Prize in Physics \"for his services to Theoretical Physics, and especially for his discovery of the law of the photoelectric effect\".", "relevance_score": 0.8697, "rerank_score": 8.429513931274414}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "ts and originality made Einstein broadly synonymous with genius. Many popular quotations are often misattributed to him.\n\nAwards and honors\nEinstein received numerous awards and honors, and in 1922, he was awarded the 1921 Nobel Prize in Physics \"for his services to Theoretical Physics, and especial", "relevance_score": 0.8581, "rerank_score": 8.261346817016602}, {"doc_id": "f43c1fd81abf", "source": "wikipedia:Albert Einstein", "excerpt": "Albert Einstein (14 March 1879 \u2013 18 April 1955) was a German-born theoretical physicist best known for developing the theory of relativity. Einstein also made important contributions to quantum theory. His mass\u2013energy equivalence formula E = mc2, which arises from special relativity, has been called", "relevance_score": 0.6594, "rerank_score": 6.792404651641846}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "The source directly states that Albert Einstein won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921 for the discovery of the law of the photoelectric effect.", "key_evidence": "Albert Einstein won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921"}, "action": "annotate", "annotation": "VERIFIED (confidence 0.92, GENERAL) \u2014 Source: general_einstein_nobel, myth_einstein_failed_school"}], "retrieval_metadata": [{"claim_id": "6f6951d8", "query_variants": [], "total_retrieved": 0, "total_after_rerank": 0, "cache_hit": true, "ensemble_used": false}, {"claim_id": "f4a47408", "query_variants": [], "total_retrieved": 0, "total_after_rerank": 0, "cache_hit": true, "ensemble_used": false}], "corrected_text": false}
{"request_id": "db04a154-5258-46d9-8ecc-926d0e0cd2b0", "timestamp": "2026-04-23T02:36:21.541596Z", "model": "default", "total_claims": 2, "verified_count": 1, "partially_supported_count": 1, "unverifiable_count": 0, "contradicted_count": 0, "pass_count": 0, "annotate_count": 1, "flagged_count": 1, "blocked_count": 0, "cache_hits": 0, "overall_confidence": 0.76, "response_blocked": false, "block_reason": null, "processing_time_ms": 39953.65, "claims": [{"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "5e8a63f1", "text": "Aspirin should not be given to children under 16 with viral infections due to the risk of Reye syndrome.", "normalized": "Aspirin is contraindicated in children under 16 with viral infections due to Reye syndrome risk.", "claim_type": "medical", "stakes": "critical", "span_start": 44, "span_end": 148, "category": "MEDICAL"}, "status": "verified", "confidence": 0.92, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "8e5cbdd828c2", "source": "medical_aspirin_reye", "excerpt": "Aspirin (acetylsalicylic acid) must NOT be given to children under 16 due to the risk of Reye's syndrome \u2014 a rare, potentially fatal condition causing acute liver failure and brain swelling. The NHS and CDC both advise paracetamol or ibuprofen as safer alternatives for fever and pain in children.", "relevance_score": 0.9403, "rerank_score": 7.421566963195801}, {"doc_id": "7d99d9fdded3", "source": "myth_aspirin_children", "excerpt": "Aspirin (acetylsalicylic acid) should NOT be given to children under 16 years of age due to the risk of Reye's syndrome, a rare but potentially fatal condition causing liver and brain damage. Ibuprofen is NOT safe to use throughout all trimesters of pregnancy. It is generally avoided in the third tr", "relevance_score": 0.8611, "rerank_score": 6.563390731811523}, {"doc_id": "d89e60753c4b", "source": "wikipedia:Influenza", "excerpt": "t. It is recommended to avoid alcohol and tobacco use while ill. Aspirin is not recommended to treat influenza in children due to an elevated risk of developing Reye syndrome. Corticosteroids are not recommended except when treating septic shock or an underlying medical condition, such as chronic ob", "relevance_score": 0.7645, "rerank_score": 4.183938503265381}, {"doc_id": "9c794b6ffab2", "source": "wikipedia:Diabetes", "excerpt": "as not been found to improve outcomes in uncomplicated diabetes. 2015 American Diabetes Association recommendations for aspirin use (based on expert consensus or clinical experience) are that low-dose aspirin use is reasonable in adults with diabetes who are at intermediate risk of cardiovascular di", "relevance_score": 0.4337, "rerank_score": -2.950425863265991}, {"doc_id": "d89e60753c4b", "source": "wikipedia:Influenza", "excerpt": "seizures and Reye syndrome can occur, most commonly in children. Influenza-associated encephalopathy can occur directly from central nervous system infection from the presence of the virus in blood and presents as sudden onset of fever with convulsions, followed by rapid progression to coma. An atyp", "relevance_score": 0.4361, "rerank_score": -3.413238048553467}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "The source directly states that aspirin is contraindicated in children under 16 due to the risk of Reye's syndrome.", "key_evidence": "Aspirin (acetylsalicylic acid) must NOT be given to children under 16 due to the risk of Reye's syndrome"}, "action": "annotate", "annotation": "VERIFIED (confidence 0.92, MEDICAL) \u2014 Source: medical_aspirin_reye, myth_aspirin_children"}, {"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "6b02d668", "text": "Bitcoin was created by Satoshi Nakamoto in 2008.", "normalized": "Bitcoin was created by Satoshi Nakamoto in 2008.", "claim_type": "statistic", "stakes": "medium", "span_start": 149, "span_end": 197, "category": "GENERAL"}, "status": "partially_supported", "confidence": 0.6, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "ca2e635a65f1", "source": "financial_bitcoin_creation", "excerpt": "Bitcoin was created in 2009 by an anonymous person or group using the pseudonym Satoshi Nakamoto. The maximum supply of Bitcoin is capped at 21 million coins. Bitcoin uses blockchain technology \u2014 a distributed ledger maintained by a decentralised network of computers (nodes). Bitcoin is NOT legal te", "relevance_score": 0.9114, "rerank_score": 7.594631671905518}, {"doc_id": "bd0ab4b7a63d", "source": "wikipedia:Cryptocurrency", "excerpt": "th solutions being cryptographically put together and published. In January 2009, bitcoin was created by pseudonymous developer Satoshi Nakamoto. It used SHA-256, a cryptographic hash function, in its proof-of-work scheme. In April 2011, Namecoin was created as an attempt at forming a decentralized ", "relevance_score": 0.8148, "rerank_score": 7.063695907592773}, {"doc_id": "bd0ab4b7a63d", "source": "wikipedia:Cryptocurrency", "excerpt": "or, more recently, Ron Paul and Tea Party-style libertarianism. Steve Bannon, who owns a \"good stake\" in bitcoin, sees cryptocurrency as a form of disruptive populism, taking control back from central authorities. Bitcoin's founder, Satoshi Nakamoto, supported the idea that cryptocurrencies go well ", "relevance_score": 0.8607, "rerank_score": 6.1053147315979}, {"doc_id": "bd0ab4b7a63d", "source": "wikipedia:Cryptocurrency", "excerpt": "hich cryptocurrencies are based was created by Satoshi Nakamoto. Within a proof-of-work system such as bitcoin, the safety, integrity, and balance of ledgers are maintained by a community of mutually distrustful parties referred to as miners. Miners use their computers to help validate and timestamp", "relevance_score": 0.6908, "rerank_score": 4.884256839752197}, {"doc_id": "bd0ab4b7a63d", "source": "wikipedia:Cryptocurrency", "excerpt": "viewpoint if we can explain it properly,\" Nakamoto said in 2008. According to the European Central Bank, the decentralization of money offered by bitcoin has its theoretical roots in the Austrian school of economics, especially with Friedrich von Hayek in his book Denationalisation of Money: The Arg", "relevance_score": 0.3861, "rerank_score": 4.86000919342041}], "contradiction_reason": "Source 7 mentions 2008, while sources 5 and 6 mention 2009.", "verification_reasoning": "The sources mention Bitcoin's creation by Satoshi Nakamoto, but the year is inconsistent, with some sources stating 2008 and others 2009.", "key_evidence": "Bitcoin was created in 2009 by an anonymous person or group using the pseudonym Satoshi Nakamoto"}, "action": "flag", "annotation": "FLAGGED \u2014 Only partially supported (confidence 0.60): The sources mention Bitcoin's creation by Satoshi Nakamoto, but the year is inconsistent, with some sources stating 2008"}], "retrieval_metadata": [{"claim_id": "5e8a63f1", "query_variants": ["Aspirin is contraindicated in children under 16 with viral infections due to Reye syndrome risk.", "Aspirin contraindication in children under 16 with viral infections Reye syndrome", "Reye syndrome risk in pediatric patients with viral infections and aspirin use"], "total_retrieved": 14, "total_after_rerank": 5, "cache_hit": false, "ensemble_used": false}, {"claim_id": "6b02d668", "query_variants": ["Bitcoin was created by Satoshi Nakamoto in 2008."], "total_retrieved": 10, "total_after_rerank": 5, "cache_hit": false, "ensemble_used": false}], "corrected_text": false}
