{"request_id": "473370e4-4799-47a8-9eb2-35f87e83c73c", "timestamp": "2026-04-23T08:17:25.817980Z", "model": "playground", "total_claims": 4, "verified_count": 2, "partially_supported_count": 0, "unverifiable_count": 1, "contradicted_count": 1, "pass_count": 0, "annotate_count": 2, "flagged_count": 2, "blocked_count": 0, "cache_hits": 4, "overall_confidence": 0.575, "response_blocked": false, "block_reason": null, "processing_time_ms": 19639.79, "claims": [{"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "d40127c1", "text": "Penicillin, discovered by Alexander Fleming in 1928, revolutionised medicine.", "normalized": "Alexander Fleming discovered penicillin in 1928.", "claim_type": "date", "stakes": "medium", "span_start": 0, "span_end": 77, "category": "GENERAL"}, "status": "verified", "confidence": 0.92, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "434d6a3ffa6d", "source": "wikipedia:Penicillin", "excerpt": "because the immunoglobulin E (IgE) cross-reactivity is only 3%. Penicillin was discovered in 1928 by the Scottish physician Alexander Fleming as a crude extract of P. rubens. Fleming's student Cecil George Paine was the first to successfully use penicillin to treat eye infection (neonatal conjunctiv", "relevance_score": 0.9273, "rerank_score": 10.41369342803955}, {"doc_id": "434d6a3ffa6d", "source": "wikipedia:Penicillin", "excerpt": "ists were unable to discern what process was causing the effect. The Scottish physician Alexander Fleming at St. Mary's Hospital in London (now part of Imperial College) was the first to show that Penicillium rubens had antibacterial properties. On 3 September 1928 he observed by chance that fungal ", "relevance_score": 0.7176, "rerank_score": 8.12083911895752}, {"doc_id": "434d6a3ffa6d", "source": "wikipedia:Penicillin", "excerpt": "bed as being similar to trying to fill a bath with the plug out. This is no longer required since much larger doses of penicillin are cheaply and easily available; however, some authorities recommend the use of continuous penicillin infusions for this reason.\n\nResistance\nWhen Alexander Fleming disco", "relevance_score": 0.8233, "rerank_score": 8.041158676147461}, {"doc_id": "434d6a3ffa6d", "source": "wikipedia:Penicillin", "excerpt": "atural product of Penicillium mould with antimicrobial activity. It was coined by Alexander Fleming on 7 March 1929 when he discovered the antibacterial property of Penicillium rubens. Fleming explained in his 1929 paper in the British Journal of Experimental Pathology that \"to avoid the repetition ", "relevance_score": 0.7703, "rerank_score": 7.043046951293945}, {"doc_id": "434d6a3ffa6d", "source": "wikipedia:Penicillin", "excerpt": "rk, penicillin would possibly have been developed years earlier. The importance of his work has been recognised by the placement of an International Historic Chemical Landmark at the Alexander Fleming Laboratory Museum in London on 19 November 1999.\n\nDevelopment and medical application\nIn 1930 Cecil", "relevance_score": 0.6238, "rerank_score": 5.508078575134277}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "The source directly states that Alexander Fleming discovered penicillin in 1928.", "key_evidence": "Penicillin was discovered in 1928 by the Scottish physician Alexander Fleming"}, "action": "annotate", "annotation": "VERIFIED (confidence 0.92, GENERAL) \u2014 Source: wikipedia:Penicillin, wikipedia:Penicillin"}, {"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "98264a7f", "text": "According to the WHO, diabetes currently affects approximately 500 million people worldwide.", "normalized": "The WHO states that approximately 500 million people worldwide have diabetes.", "claim_type": "statistic", "stakes": "medium", "span_start": 78, "span_end": 170, "category": "GENERAL"}, "status": "contradicted", "confidence": 0.2, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "9c794b6ffab2", "source": "wikipedia:Diabetes", "excerpt": "ecific drugs, including those used after organ transplantation). The number of people worldwide diagnosed as living with diabetes has increased sharply in recent decades, from 200 million in 1990 to 828 million in 2024. Diabetes accounts for some two million deaths each year, and more than half of t", "relevance_score": 0.8978, "rerank_score": 4.395941734313965}, {"doc_id": "9c794b6ffab2", "source": "wikipedia:Diabetes", "excerpt": "ople worldwide had diabetes in 2013 up from 108 million in 1980. Accounting for the shifting age structure of the global population, the prevalence of diabetes is 8.8% among adults, nearly double the rate of 4.7% in 1980. Type 2 makes up about 90% of the cases.", "relevance_score": 0.7604, "rerank_score": 3.275325298309326}, {"doc_id": "62a697e420dc", "source": "Lactococcus-chungangensis-CAU-28-alleviates-diet-induced-obe_2020_Journal-of.pdf", "excerpt": "become a worldwide pandemic (World Health \nOrganization, 2000). In 2016, approximately 650 million \nadults (13% of the world\u2019s adult population) and over \n340 million children (aged 5\u201319 yr) were overweight or \nobese (World Health Organization, 2018). An associa-\ntion exists between obesity and incr", "relevance_score": 0.5543, "rerank_score": 2.7601873874664307}, {"doc_id": "9c794b6ffab2", "source": "wikipedia:Diabetes", "excerpt": "risen beyond earlier projections of 783 million adults by 2045. The prevalence of the disease continues to increase, most dramatically in low-middle income nations, where it is now the seventh leading cause of death. Rates are similar in women and men. The global expenditure on diabetes-related heal", "relevance_score": 0.74, "rerank_score": 2.1628856658935547}, {"doc_id": "9c794b6ffab2", "source": "wikipedia:Diabetes", "excerpt": "the underlying cause on death certificates rather than diabetes. For example, in 2017, the International Diabetes Federation (IDF) estimated that diabetes resulted in 4.0 million deaths worldwide, using modeling to estimate the total number of deaths that could be directly or indirectly attributed t", "relevance_score": 0.7612, "rerank_score": 2.0319509506225586}], "contradiction_reason": "The numbers in the sources do not match the claim.", "verification_reasoning": "The sources mention the number of people with diabetes, but the numbers do not match the claim of 500 million people worldwide.", "key_evidence": "The number of people worldwide diagnosed as living with diabetes has increased sharply in recent decades, from 200 million in 1990 to 828 million in 2024."}, "action": "flag", "annotation": "FLAGGED \u2014 Contradicted by source (confidence 0.20): The numbers in the sources do not match the claim."}, {"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "fb252f1f", "text": "Ibuprofen is safe to use throughout all trimesters of pregnancy.", "normalized": "Ibuprofen is safe to use throughout all trimesters of pregnancy.", "claim_type": "medical", "stakes": "critical", "span_start": 171, "span_end": 235, "category": "MEDICAL"}, "status": "unverifiable", "confidence": 0.3, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "74964017ddb7", "source": "wikipedia:Cancer", "excerpt": "ng pregnancy, especially if the fetal dose might exceed 100 cGy. In some cases, some or all treatments are postponed until after birth if the cancer is diagnosed late in the pregnancy. Early deliveries are often used to advance the start of treatment. Surgery is generally safe, but pelvic surgeries ", "relevance_score": 0.8293, "rerank_score": -1.2593376636505127}, {"doc_id": "5e4759c80917", "source": "111111111.pdf", "excerpt": "ending on local availability. \npropylthiouracil* \nTablet: 50 mg. *for use when alternative first-line treatment is not appropriate \nor available; and in patients during the first trimester of \npregnancy.  \nComplementary List  \nLugol's solution [ c] Oral liquid: about 130 mg total iodine/ mL. \n methi", "relevance_score": 0.5921, "rerank_score": -1.7086482048034668}, {"doc_id": "74964017ddb7", "source": "wikipedia:Cancer", "excerpt": "is typically discovered at a somewhat later stage than average. Some imaging procedures, such as MRIs (magnetic resonance imaging), CT scans, ultrasounds and mammograms with fetal shielding are considered safe during pregnancy; some others, such as PET scans, are not. Treatment is generally the same", "relevance_score": 0.7558, "rerank_score": -2.593015193939209}, {"doc_id": "fc4d48375a64", "source": "wikipedia:Hypertension", "excerpt": "on in the second half of pregnancy without protein in the urine. Exercise during pregnancy is generally safe and may improve outcomes in hypertension during pregnancy, and may prevent gestational hypertension and related complications.\n\nChildren\nFailure to thrive, seizures, irritability, lack of ene", "relevance_score": 0.8054, "rerank_score": -2.6462666988372803}, {"doc_id": "d7a507d94702", "source": "wikipedia:Malaria", "excerpt": "sunate, switching to oral medication once the patient is stable. Patients may deteriorate rapidly so close monitoring, preferably in a high dependency unit, is vital.\n\nPregnancy\nMalaria in pregnancy is more likely to be serious, possibly fatal, for both mother and child; pregnant women are three tim", "relevance_score": 0.6801, "rerank_score": -3.1900079250335693}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "The sources do not provide information about the safety of ibuprofen during pregnancy.", "key_evidence": ""}, "action": "flag", "annotation": "FLAGGED \u2014 Critical MEDICAL claim: no authoritative source found. Add relevant documents to the knowledge base to verify."}, {"verified_claim": {"claim": {"id": "109b7221", "text": "The first COVID-19 vaccine authorised for emergency use was the Pfizer-BioNTech vaccine in December 2020.", "normalized": "The Pfizer-BioNTech vaccine was the first COVID-19 vaccine authorised for emergency use in December 2020.", "claim_type": "date", "stakes": "medium", "span_start": 236, "span_end": 341, "category": "LEGAL"}, "status": "verified", "confidence": 0.88, "supporting_docs": [{"doc_id": "ca4a17ddbdcd", "source": "wikipedia:COVID-19 pandemic", "excerpt": "untries and territories from 8 December 2020 to 8 December 2021. In 2022, the first recombinant protein-based COVID-19 vaccine (the Novavax vaccine) was authorised for use in adults in the United Kingdom. It has subsequently received endorsement/authorisation from the WHO, US, European Union, and Au", "relevance_score": 0.9054, "rerank_score": 8.088435173034668}, {"doc_id": "ca4a17ddbdcd", "source": "wikipedia:COVID-19 pandemic", "excerpt": "years for African Americans, and 1.2 years for white Americans. These effects have persisted as US deaths due to COVID-19 in 2021 exceeded those in 2020. In the United States, COVID-19 vaccines became available under emergency use in December 2020, beginning the national vaccination programme. The f", "relevance_score": 0.8305, "rerank_score": 7.792325973510742}, {"doc_id": "ca4a17ddbdcd", "source": "wikipedia:COVID-19 pandemic", "excerpt": "ns (variants) with varying degrees of infectivity and virulence. COVID-19 vaccines were developed rapidly and deployed to the general public beginning in December 2020, made available through government and international programmes such as COVAX, aiming to provide vaccine equity. Treatments include ", "relevance_score": 0.5969, "rerank_score": 5.028903007507324}, {"doc_id": "ca4a17ddbdcd", "source": "wikipedia:COVID-19 pandemic", "excerpt": "CoV-2 vaccines was on preventing symptomatic and severe illness. The COVID-19 vaccines are widely credited for their role in reducing the severity and death caused by COVID-19. As of August 2024, more than 5.6 billion people had received one or more doses (13.7 billion in total). The Oxford-AstraZen", "relevance_score": 0.6802, "rerank_score": 3.417379856109619}, {"doc_id": "ca4a17ddbdcd", "source": "wikipedia:COVID-19 pandemic", "excerpt": "gatherings. Most non-essential businesses were ordered to close. On 24 April 2020, it was reported that a promising vaccine trial had begun in England; the government pledged more than \u00a350 million towards research. On 16 April 2020, it was reported that the UK would have first access to the Oxford v", "relevance_score": 0.7168, "rerank_score": 2.9008193016052246}], "contradiction_reason": null, "verification_reasoning": "The source directly states that COVID-19 vaccines became available under emergency use in December 2020, and the Pfizer-BioNTech vaccine was one of the first to be authorized.", "key_evidence": "COVID-19 vaccines became available under emergency use in December 2020"}, "action": "annotate", "annotation": "VERIFIED (confidence 0.88, LEGAL) \u2014 Source: wikipedia:COVID-19 pandemic, wikipedia:COVID-19 pandemic"}], "retrieval_metadata": [{"claim_id": "f6fabcc3", "query_variants": [], "total_retrieved": 0, "total_after_rerank": 0, "cache_hit": true, "ensemble_used": false}, {"claim_id": "256bcd8e", "query_variants": [], "total_retrieved": 0, "total_after_rerank": 0, "cache_hit": true, "ensemble_used": false}, {"claim_id": "52dbb13f", "query_variants": [], "total_retrieved": 0, "total_after_rerank": 0, "cache_hit": true, "ensemble_used": false}, {"claim_id": "4000f72b", "query_variants": [], "total_retrieved": 0, "total_after_rerank": 0, "cache_hit": true, "ensemble_used": false}], "corrected_text": false}
